Body size medium (body length 
12–15 mm
), hair (pubescence) moderately short and even, wings clear. Colour pattern of the hair of the body predominantly black. Head black except for yellow in a tuft on the face ventral to the antennal base, on the vertex, and posteriorly around the base of the proboscis. Thoracic dorsum with broad anterior and posterior yellow bands of nearly equal breadth and without black hairs intermixed, the black band between the wing bases without yellow hairs intermixed; side of the thorax (mesepisternum) yellow anterior to the wing base; legs with the long hairs intermixed black and pale. T1–2 yellow without any black hairs; T3 entirely black; T4–7 entirely orange-red. Genitalia (
Fig. 200
) with the gonostylus shorter than broad, its inner basal projection reduced to a short stub; volsella with the inner distal corner broadly produced but without a narrow hook.

This is one of the highest recorded bumblebees in the world, at an elevation of ca 5640 m a.s.l. ( Williams 2018 : along with
B. tanguticus
). Specimens in the NHMUK collection labelled “ Sikkim ” are actually from Xizang (“Kampa Dzong” = Gampa Dzong, 28.271° N , 88.513°E ).
